1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:03,810
(Episode 138)

2
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:08,350
Wait here.
I'll go check on the smuggling ship.

3
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:10,350
Wait. I'll go with you.

4
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:12,450
I'm scared to be alone.

5
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:16,190
It's okay. I'll be right back.

6
00:00:42,950 --> 00:00:43,980
Here.

7
00:00:44,620 --> 00:00:45,720
This is for you.

8
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,520
What is this, Chairman?

9
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:51,920
You went through a lot
while I was bedridden, didn't you?

10
00:00:52,220 --> 00:00:53,220
Not at all.

11
00:00:54,630 --> 00:00:58,660
This is for you, Choi Ha Joon.
Take a look.

12
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,470
(Dream Hotel Dividend)

13
00:01:06,870 --> 00:01:08,340
(Dream Hotel Dividend)

14
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:12,840
1.89 billion dollars?

15
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:17,150
Your grandfather,
Chairman Choi Myung Chul, and I...

16
00:01:17,580 --> 00:01:20,080
founded this hotel
on a 30-70 ownership split.

17
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:24,960
Your grandfather had terminal cancer,

18
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,160
so he trusted me and asked me
to look after you...

19
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:29,930
when you were just a baby.

20
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:32,060
Yes.

21
00:01:32,230 --> 00:01:36,400
When I heard you were adopted overseas,

22
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:40,040
I should've found you, no matter what.

23
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:41,940
I'm sorry.

24
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:43,270
Not at all.

25
00:01:43,780 --> 00:01:47,550
I heard the whole story
from Jang Mi's father and the nanny.

26
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:50,080
For the past 30 years,

27
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:54,620
you've held onto these dividends
without ever touching them.

28
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:58,090
That tells me everything I need to know
about your sincerity, Chairman.

29
00:01:58,790 --> 00:01:59,890
Thank you, Chairman.

30
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:03,390
There's nothing to thank me for.

31
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,130
It's all rightfully yours.

32
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,900
The principal, plus VIP compound interest.

33
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,370
And the hotel shares are also...

34
00:02:13,670 --> 00:02:14,940
in a title trust under your name.

35
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:17,680
With that money,

36
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:22,980
uproot the corruption in Dream Hotel
that Chae Hwa Young caused,

37
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:26,820
and build the hotel
that you and Jang Mi want.

38
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:29,020
I'll give you my full support.

39
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:31,320
Thank you, Chairman.

40
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:36,430
Thank you, Han Young Ja.

41
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:40,400
I heard that you told the police...

42
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:41,830
about my true intentions.

43
00:02:41,970 --> 00:02:44,400
Just because you revealed
the recorded phone call,

44
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,640
don't you dare think
you've paid for all your sins.

45
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:54,150
I know.
That's why I'm paying the price like this.

46
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,680
What on earth is love?

47
00:02:57,580 --> 00:03:00,050
Just to protect
that pathetic Chae Hwa Young,

48
00:03:00,950 --> 00:03:04,290
you lost the professorship
you worked so hard for...

49
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:07,560
and hit rock bottom just to pay the price?

50
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:09,660
Is she really worth all that?

51
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,800
Tell me about it.

52
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:18,600
I'm studying it myself.
It's a study of life and people...

53
00:03:19,970 --> 00:03:21,170
that I'm learning the hard way.

54
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,540
I think...

55
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:27,180
I'll work on my dissertation in here.

56
00:03:28,010 --> 00:03:29,410
Good for you for having something to do.

57
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,720
Anyway, I'll represent you pro bono.

58
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:35,890
But, Kang Nam Bong,

59
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,420
for what you've done,

60
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,160
you had better truly repent.

61
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,560
Honey.

62
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,100
I'm sorry.

63
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:51,170
And...

64
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:53,710
thank you.

65
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,050
What?

66
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:05,880
Mom.

67
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:10,990
What's this? This was hidden in there.

68
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:14,060
It's a micro-recorder.

69
00:04:14,330 --> 00:04:17,600
But why would this be
in Chae Hwa Young's room?

70
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:19,160
Let's give it a listen.

71
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,310
Jang Mi.

72
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:29,410
You bastard.

73
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,380
What are you doing?

74
00:04:34,910 --> 00:04:35,910
Kang Jun Ho.

75
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,920
Listen carefully...

76
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,320
what you did to my Seo Rin.

77
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:43,720
You're also to blame
for Seo Rin's wrongful death in surgery.

78
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:51,130
Was that Jun Ho on the phone?

79
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:54,070
I didn't mishear that, did I?
Jun Ho just asked me out on a date!

80
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:58,940
See? Your persistence paid off.
Jun Ho finally realized how you feel.

81
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,670
Make sure you look your best tomorrow.

82
00:05:01,010 --> 00:05:03,640
Let's schedule your plastic surgery soon,
okay?

83
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:07,010
Okay. Mom, where are my pills?
Give me my pills.

84
00:05:07,210 --> 00:05:11,720
You need to take these to lose weight.
They'll make you slim and beautiful.

85
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:14,920
But these aren't addictive, are they?

86
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:16,650
Why would I give you weird medication?

87
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,320
- Kang Jun Ho.
- I made sure it's safe.

88
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,890
You're no different from Chae Hwa Young.

89
00:05:21,330 --> 00:05:23,360
You drove Seo Rin to her death.

90
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:26,360
Because you lied and asked her on a date,

91
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:30,300
Seo Rin took the pills from Chae Hwa Young
without suspecting a thing.

92
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,740
Because of you.

93
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,270
I...

94
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,640
I had no idea
CEO Chae would even give her pills.

95
00:05:37,810 --> 00:05:39,880
I did resent CEO Chae...

96
00:05:40,910 --> 00:05:41,910
Yes.

97
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:45,080
Because she told me to recommend
a rural clinic to Seo Rin.

98
00:05:47,590 --> 00:05:48,590
What?

99
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:51,460
I swear, I had no idea
this would happen to Seo Rin.

100
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:55,030
- It's true.
- Ignorance isn't an excuse.

101
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:57,960
The one who made my Seo Rin
go to the rural clinic...

102
00:05:58,730 --> 00:06:00,160
was you, Kang Jun Ho?

103
00:06:02,170 --> 00:06:03,840
Why did you do it? Why?

104
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,800
How could you
trample all over her love for you?

105
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,310
How could you?

106
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,640
Oh, poor Seo Rin.

107
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:17,880
She was killed by the very people
she loved so much.

108
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:20,550
Seo Rin...

109
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:23,320
was killed by you,
Kang Jun Ho, whom she trusted completely,

110
00:06:23,790 --> 00:06:25,620
and by Chae Hwa Young.

111
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:29,860
By you, Kang Jun Ho,
the one she loved most of all.

112
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,360
Jang Mi.

113
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,500
I didn't know...

114
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,500
Seo Rin would die like that.

115
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,940
I've regretted it over and over again.

116
00:06:41,770 --> 00:06:43,340
If I could turn back time,

117
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,180
I would have stopped CEO Chae,
no matter what.

118
00:06:47,810 --> 00:06:48,810
I'm sorry.

119
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,890
I'm sorry, Jang Mi.

120
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,890
Don't apologize to me.

121
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,860
Apologize to Seo Rin
who died so wrongfully.

122
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,960
And to do that,

123
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,800
you need to step up
and make Chae Hwa Young turn herself in...

124
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,700
and pay for your crime as well.

125
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:12,840
I hope those tears you're crying are real.

126
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,500
Why were you so determined...

127
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,600
to marry Jang Mi instead of Seo Rin?

128
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:46,270
Were you really in love with Jang Mi?

129
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:48,940
Now that I think about it,
I don't even know myself.

130
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,780
Whether I ever really loved Jang Mi.

131
00:07:57,580 --> 00:08:00,120
Why I pushed Seo Rin away so much.

132
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:03,860
Perhaps if Seo Rin had said she loved you,

133
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:07,890
I probably would have said
I loved her too.

134
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,500
So in the end,
you were just jealous of me?

135
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:13,500
You just wanted to take what was mine?

136
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:15,070
While I had to...

137
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:18,440
struggle with all my might...

138
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,110
for things I could barely hope to obtain,

139
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:24,110
you never had to work hard...

140
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,380
to get everything so easily.

141
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,480
People...

142
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,850
always liked you
because you were so bright.

143
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:33,820
And our parents...

144
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:39,320
were always at ease with you
and loved you like their real son.

145
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,790
I always just watched, filled with envy.

146
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:46,200
No, that's because you were so standoffish
that they found you hard to approach.

147
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:49,070
You know how much our parents loved you.

148
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:50,840
What would I know?

149
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:55,710
I felt like I was drinking seawater.
The more I drank, the thirstier I got.

150
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:58,810
For me, it was always...

151
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,210
an insatiable hunger.

152
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:06,750
And all I did was
struggle to fill that void.

153
00:09:07,890 --> 00:09:08,890
I don't know.

154
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:11,720
Maybe you're just trying
to justify your actions,

155
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:15,330
or maybe I'm the one
who really doesn't understand you.

156
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:17,400
But one thing's for sure.

157
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:20,460
Just because someone was abandoned
by their parents as a child like you...

158
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:22,330
doesn't mean they all
compromise with injustice.

159
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,280
Kang Hyuk.

160
00:09:33,310 --> 00:09:34,350
I'm cold.

161
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:36,080
I need some medicine.

162
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:43,850
Just hang in there.

163
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,960
I'll get you some medicine no matter what.

164
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:59,100
Drinking on an empty stomach
will mess you up.

165
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:02,010
Have some food with it, Jun Ho.

166
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:04,610
Do you want to join us, Mom?

167
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:05,980
Maybe I will.

168
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:11,380
(Restricted Number)

169
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,240
Hello.

170
00:10:38,810 --> 00:10:40,210
Jun Ho, it's me.

171
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:43,910
- Manager Lee.
- I didn't want to call you,

172
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,750
but I had no other choice.

173
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:48,920
Your mother is very sick.

174
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,260
She has a high fever
and is struggling to breathe.

175
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,720
So...

176
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:55,260
I need to buy medicine,
but I have no money.

177
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,260
Help me, Jun Ho.

178
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,770
- Just turn yourselves in.
- What are you talking about?

179
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:03,900
If she turns herself in now, she will
spend the rest of her life in prison.

180
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:07,510
- So how can she turn herself in?
- Will she live on the run forever?

181
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:09,910
You said she's sick.

182
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:14,010
She should surrender
and hope for leniency.

183
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:15,050
Leniency?

184
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:17,620
Leniency? To heck with leniency.

185
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:19,480
Those darn cops...

186
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:23,290
They don't even have the actual weapon
used to strike Oh Bok Gil.

187
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:24,290
There's no physical evidence.

188
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,290
In the end, all they can pin on her...

189
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:29,060
is soliciting Seo Rin's murder
and the attempted murder of Chairman Ma.

190
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:31,300
- That's it.
- What do you mean?

191
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,330
The weapon used to kill Oh Bok Gil...

192
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,840
Do you mean the wrench?

193
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:42,110
I was under the impression
the police already had it.

194
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:45,280
That fool Ssangkal
gave his girlfriend a fake.

195
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,980
This is the real wrench, Chae Hwa Young.

196
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:55,790
This...

197
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:58,320
is the proof you struck Oh Bok Gil.

198
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:01,230
The real murder weapon...

199
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:05,200
- is in my possession.
- Wait, what do you mean...

200
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:07,570
So you're saying...

201
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:09,570
you have the real wrench?

202
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,540
I don't need to
get into the details with you.

203
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,970
We missed the smuggling ship.

204
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:18,710
I need money, Jun Ho.

205
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,210
Where should I bring the money?

206
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:28,190
<i>Three bears live in a house</i>

207
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:32,420
<i>Papa Bear, Mama Bear, and Baby Bear</i>

208
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:36,760
<i>Papa Bear is chubby</i>

209
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:41,130
<i>Mama Bear is skinny</i>

210
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:45,140
<i>Baby Bear is so cute</i>

211
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:49,110
<i>Good job, good job, well done</i>

212
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:51,180
- You're doing great, Bo Ra.
- You really are.

213
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:54,010
- Bo Ra's a natural.
- She is.

214
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,980
- Here.
- Hold on.

215
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:59,220
- Okay, Bo Ra, should we sing another one?
- Here you go.

216
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,860
I suddenly started thinking a lot
about Seo Rin.

217
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:09,130
And about my husband, too, of course.

218
00:13:09,430 --> 00:13:10,430
That's good.

219
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:14,060
Jang Mi, I think we might be able to find
the real wrench.

220
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,970
What? What do you mean, find the wrench?

221
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,740
The one we lost last time was a fake.

222
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:21,070
It turns out
Lee Kang Hyuk has the real one.

223
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:22,470
What?

224
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,680
How much are they asking for?

225
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:37,890
I'll pull together as much money as I can,
so tell me where you're meeting them.

226
00:13:38,090 --> 00:13:40,520
- I'll go.
- You're going?

227
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:42,330
What do you mean?

228
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:44,160
You're now under investigation
without detention.

229
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:46,360
I pulled strings to keep you here.

230
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,670
But if you meet Chae Hwa Young
and give her the money,

231
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:51,070
the moment you try to escape
with those devils,

232
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:56,140
your release will be revoked,
a nationwide APB will be put out on you,

233
00:13:56,770 --> 00:13:58,540
and an arrest warrant will be issued
immediately.

234
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:01,680
If you get caught,
you'll be considered a flight risk,

235
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:03,650
and sent straight to jail.

236
00:14:03,650 --> 00:14:06,520
Plus, they'll tack on extra charges
for defiance,

237
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,920
which will make your sentence
even harsher.

238
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,520
Of course. As a lawyer, you know all this.

239
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:17,660
If you're going,

240
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,430
take me with you.

241
00:14:20,530 --> 00:14:21,530
I'll...

242
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,630
go with you.

243
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:27,910
I'll get on my knees
and beg Chae Hwa Young.

244
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:30,310
I'll tell her she can have
my entire fortune...

245
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:33,310
if she just leaves my son alone.

246
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:39,450
- Mother.
- I...

247
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:44,360
I can't live without you either.

248
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,320
All right.

249
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:48,090
I'll...

250
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:51,630
help Chae Hwa Young
and Lee Kang Hyuk escape.

251
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:54,700
And then,
the charge for aiding a fugitive...

252
00:14:56,070 --> 00:14:57,330
I'll take it.

253
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,270
You stay out of trouble.

254
00:15:00,070 --> 00:15:01,970
Don't get hurt anymore.

255
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,780
It'll kill me.

256
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,640
Mom, please don't do this.

257
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:09,410
I'm not worth it.

258
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:12,220
You know...

259
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,390
how much I've hurt you all this time...

260
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:16,850
and how much trouble I've caused you.

261
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,890
Why would you go this far
for someone like me?

262
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,930
You know...

263
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:25,360
I have Chae Hwa Young's blood in me.

264
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,360
I'm a bad person.

265
00:15:39,210 --> 00:15:41,510
Because I love you.

266
00:15:47,950 --> 00:15:49,590
It doesn't matter whose blood you have.

267
00:15:50,890 --> 00:15:52,420
You are my son.

268
00:15:52,990 --> 00:15:54,330
What mother...

269
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:57,630
would just stand by
and watch her own child...

270
00:15:57,630 --> 00:15:59,100
walk into the fires of hell?

271
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,830
Jun Ho.

272
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:04,030
Seeing you like this...

273
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,740
I can't bear to watch it anymore.

274
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,040
It's tearing my heart apart.

275
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:11,740
Please.

276
00:16:12,410 --> 00:16:14,280
Please, just stop.

277
00:16:17,650 --> 00:16:18,650
Jun Ho.

278
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,290
Convince Chae Hwa Young
to turn herself in.

279
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:24,420
You've always been a part of our family.

280
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,020
Right?

281
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:38,670
Jun Ho.

282
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:41,000
Bring the wrench with you
when you come here.

283
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:44,510
Once you bring the money,
we can leave the country immediately,

284
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:46,510
so I'll just toss it
in the ocean on our way out.

285
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,990
The password is your birthday.

286
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,720
Dad.

287
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:33,260
I'm sorry for everything, Jang Mi.

288
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:38,100
Thanks, Jun Ho.

289
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,770
Hwa Young.

290
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:50,110
- Yes?
- Jun Ho is coming.

291
00:17:50,410 --> 00:17:53,540
- He said he's bringing money and all.
- Help me up...

292
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:01,050
Did you say my Jun Ho is coming? Really?

293
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:04,890
When Jun Ho gets here,

294
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:07,360
he'll probably have to leave with us.

295
00:18:07,690 --> 00:18:08,860
What are you talking about?

296
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:11,230
Does that mean Jun Ho...

297
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,800
will have to live as a fugitive like us?

298
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,900
No.

299
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,630
What are you talking about?
We have to send him back.

300
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,600
Jun Ho is currently being investigated
without detention.

301
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:20,940
But if he brings the money here,

302
00:18:21,940 --> 00:18:23,610
he'll never be able to go back.

303
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,640
His crime will become even more serious.

304
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:28,250
My poor baby... What am I going to do?

305
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:31,320
How could I drag Jun Ho into this?

306
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:35,220
But it's better than living
the rest of our lives missing him.

307
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,550
We can take him with us
and do right by him.

308
00:18:37,990 --> 00:18:40,860
Like you said, we just have to get
back on our feet, no matter what.

309
00:18:42,530 --> 00:18:45,060
You're right. For our Jun Ho's sake,

310
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:47,030
I'm going to
live the rest of my life well.

311
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:50,070
A mirror. Where's a mirror?

312
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,340
I'm seeing my son after so long.

313
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,970
- I can't look this shabby.
- But...

314
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:59,280
- do you feel better now?
- Don't tell Jun Ho I'm not well.

315
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,980
I don't want him to worry.

316
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,210
Eat slowly.

317
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:36,150
You'll get an upset stomach.

318
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:38,420
How did you shake the cops?

319
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,880
I made sure I stayed away
from places with CCTV.

320
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:42,690
Anyway,

321
00:19:43,350 --> 00:19:44,860
are you leaving tonight?

322
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:47,790
Yes. Did you bring the money?

323
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,160
Yes.

324
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:53,200
- It's in a bag in the parking lot.
- More importantly,

325
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,770
are Oh Jang Mi, Kang Baek Ho,
and Jung Suk Hee...

326
00:19:56,470 --> 00:19:57,870
bothering you?

327
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:59,700
Aren't they threatening
to throw you in prison?

328
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:02,740
My mother is representing me as my lawyer.

329
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:05,080
Kang Jun Ho.

330
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:06,510
Han Young Ja is your mother?

331
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,580
How dare you say that in front of me?

332
00:20:08,850 --> 00:20:12,220
Have you forgotten that Han Young Ja
sided with Jung Suk Hee...

333
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:13,720
and cost me 30 million dollars?

334
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:15,890
You be careful, too.

335
00:20:15,890 --> 00:20:18,290
That woman, Han Young Ja,
is so cold-blooded,

336
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:19,890
she wouldn't even bleed
if you stabbed her.

337
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,130
Don't say things like that.

338
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:28,400
She's agonized a lot because of me.

339
00:20:28,570 --> 00:20:30,670
Are you going to keep taking her side
in front of me?

340
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:33,970
I'm your mother, Chae Hwa Young.

341
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:35,970
And what exactly have you done for me?

342
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:40,080
When I was sick, did you ever stay
by my side and nurse me all night?

343
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,810
You abandoned me when I was a baby...

344
00:20:43,380 --> 00:20:45,150
and came back only to brand me
with the scarlet letter...

345
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:46,850
of being a murderer's son.

346
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,820
Jun Ho.

347
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:50,920
- Stop it.
- You.

348
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:53,720
Do you even know what I had to do
because of you?

349
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:55,560
Did you steal Seo Rin for me?

350
00:20:57,490 --> 00:21:00,600
Did you push Jung Suk Hee
off a cliff for me?

351
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,640
Did you have Oh Bok Gil killed for me?

352
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:08,170
Because of me...

353
00:21:09,470 --> 00:21:11,270
Did you kill Seo Rin because of me?

354
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,210
You're the kind of person...

355
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:17,310
who would use her own son
to try to kill someone.

356
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,520
To save yourself,

357
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:22,490
you murdered the daughter you raised
for 30 years.

358
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:23,550
Shut up.

359
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:25,860
Why did you hit me?

360
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,590
Did I strike a nerve?

361
00:21:29,790 --> 00:21:31,600
It's not too late.

362
00:21:32,830 --> 00:21:35,470
Please, turn yourself in
and pay for your crimes.

363
00:21:36,170 --> 00:21:40,170
I didn't want you to live a life
at rock bottom.

364
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:43,570
I wanted you to be at the very top,

365
00:21:44,340 --> 00:21:46,740
looking down on everyone else.

366
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:51,010
How can you resent me
when you don't even understand how I feel?

367
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,280
Do you have any idea how I feel?

368
00:21:54,380 --> 00:21:55,420
Jun Ho.

369
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:59,020
Let's go get the money bag. Hurry.

370
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:01,760
Jun Ho.

371
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:03,990
Don't resent me.

372
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:09,070
I didn't know it would turn out like this.
I didn't do it on purpose.

373
00:22:27,050 --> 00:22:28,050
Hey.

374
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:30,720
Did you have to
break your mother's heart like that?

375
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,990
Do you think she wanted this to happen?

376
00:22:35,090 --> 00:22:37,360
You brought the wrench, right?

377
00:22:38,130 --> 00:22:39,660
I have to get rid of it quickly.

378
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,030
I gave it...

379
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,940
to Baek Ho as evidence.

380
00:22:46,340 --> 00:22:48,870
- And there is no bag of money.
- Are you crazy?

381
00:22:49,610 --> 00:22:52,740
How could you do this to your own mother?

382
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:54,540
Are you trying to get us all killed?

383
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:56,610
How many more people have to die
for you to be satisfied?

384
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,980
I said I wanted Dream.

385
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:01,690
I never said
I wanted murderers for parents.

386
00:23:02,490 --> 00:23:04,350
Now, please, come to your senses.

387
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,630
You punk.
How could you betray us like this?

388
00:23:16,330 --> 00:23:18,470
Lee Kang Hyuk.

389
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:20,040
Lee Kang Hyuk.

390
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:22,110
Get out. Lee Kang Hyuk, get out.

391
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:25,240
Lee Kang Hyuk.

392
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:28,210
Lee Kang Hyuk.

393
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:35,690
Chae Hwa Young.

394
00:23:35,690 --> 00:23:36,690
Freeze.

395
00:23:37,150 --> 00:23:38,220
Get her.

396
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:42,790
Chae Hwa Young.
So you were hiding in here like a mole.

397
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:45,430
What? How did you all find me?

398
00:23:48,270 --> 00:23:49,300
Jun Ho.

399
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:51,740
It was Jun Ho. He betrayed me.

400
00:23:52,770 --> 00:23:55,510
Let go of me. I'm innocent.
I said, I'm innocent.

401
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,010
You're innocent?

402
00:23:57,010 --> 00:23:59,240
Seo Rin is watching from above,
you murderer.

403
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,950
That's ridiculous, Oh Jang Mi.
This is all your fault.

404
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:03,510
If you'd never appeared...

405
00:24:03,510 --> 00:24:05,850
No, if twins had never been born,

406
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:07,180
and only Seo Rin had been born,

407
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:09,320
- none of this would have happened.
- What was that?

408
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:11,820
That's right.
It's all because of Jung Suk Hee.

409
00:24:12,190 --> 00:24:15,290
If that witch hadn't caused the death
of the son I had with Dong Seok,

410
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:18,400
- I would never have ended up like this.
- You've got it all wrong.

411
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:22,000
The start of all this horrible misery
was you, and you alone.

412
00:24:22,370 --> 00:24:25,270
- It was all because of your vile greed.
- That's ridiculous.

413
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:29,870
I was just trying to get what I wanted.
How is that a crime?

414
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:32,080
Is it a crime
to want to shine the brightest?

415
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:35,080
Anyone in my shoes
would've done the same thing.

416
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:37,510
Are all of you so pure and sinless?

417
00:24:38,380 --> 00:24:41,180
If anyone thinks they can judge me,
step forward.

418
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:44,990
No one is completely without sin.

419
00:24:45,790 --> 00:24:49,460
I'm not ashamed.
I was only being true to my desires.

420
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:51,860
Shut up.
What kind of twisted logic is that?

421
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:55,530
- You're a murderer.
- Oh Jang Mi. Take a look at yourself.

422
00:24:56,070 --> 00:24:58,640
Are you really so pure,
with nothing to be ashamed of?

423
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:03,210
If you were in my shoes,
you'd have done the exact same thing.

424
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:07,110
When you see a brilliant light,
would you really just look away?

425
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:11,480
It's the circumstances
that lead people to sin.

426
00:25:12,380 --> 00:25:15,220
I was just doing my best
to follow that light.

427
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:19,260
No one has the right
to judge me for my sins.

428
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,290
Just because people want things...

429
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,290
doesn't mean
they resort to murder like you.

430
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:27,000
No matter what, murder is unforgivable.
Do you know why?

431
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:30,430
Because the dead can never come back.

432
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:33,270
No matter how much you regret
what you've done,

433
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:37,270
- you can't bring someone back to life.
- My conscience is clear.

434
00:25:37,710 --> 00:25:39,280
I've done nothing wrong.

435
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:42,510
My only crime
was living life to the fullest.

436
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:47,580
Chae Hwa Young,
for soliciting the murders of Ma Seo Rin,

437
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:48,920
Kim Bum Seok, and Noh Cheol Bong,

438
00:25:49,090 --> 00:25:50,890
for breach of trust that caused
massive losses to the company...

439
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:53,890
by illegally selling assets
of the Dream Hotel,

440
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:57,160
and for the murder of Oh Bok Gil,
you are under arrest.

441
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:59,530
You have the right to an attorney...

442
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:03,300
"Murder?" Why would I kill anyone?
I've never killed anyone.

443
00:26:04,370 --> 00:26:05,440
Do you have proof?

444
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:09,840
How can the police just make accusations
without any proof?

445
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,780
I'll sue every last one of you.

446
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:14,580
This evidence
has bloodstains from Oh Bok Gil,

447
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:17,180
and your fingerprints are an exact match.

448
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:20,620
This is irrefutable evidence of murder.

449
00:26:20,950 --> 00:26:22,120
That can't be...

450
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,720
I'm sure I cleaned up everything...

451
00:26:25,360 --> 00:26:28,220
Does that mean Lee Kang Hyuk tricked me?

452
00:26:28,890 --> 00:26:31,660
Lee Kang Hyuk, you betrayed me?

453
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:35,370
Chae Hwa Young,
you have the right to remain silent.

454
00:26:35,370 --> 00:26:38,270
- Any statement you make...
- What have I done wrong? Let go of me.

455
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,900
If I'm guilty of anything,
it all started with meeting Oh Jang Mi.

456
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:42,770
It's all your fault, Oh Jang Mi.

457
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:46,040
It's your fault.
It's all because I met you.

458
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:48,310
Let go. Let go of me.

459
00:27:05,030 --> 00:27:06,230
Grandfather.

460
00:27:07,030 --> 00:27:08,060
Mom.

461
00:27:09,630 --> 00:27:12,940
Chae Hwa Young who killed
my dad Oh Bok Gil and Seo Rin...

462
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:15,370
has finally been caught.

463
00:27:17,910 --> 00:27:18,910
Jang Mi.

464
00:27:21,010 --> 00:27:22,480
You've worked so hard.

465
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:29,420
Mom.

466
00:28:03,290 --> 00:28:04,950
(The First Man)

467
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:08,020
Hey, Chae Hwa Young.
I'm ruined because of you.

468
00:28:08,090 --> 00:28:09,790
Let go. Jin Hong Ju, get off me.

469
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:11,800
I'll make you pay for what you did
to my mother.

470
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:15,630
- You can't reach Jang Mi?
- Did you say Chae Hwa Young escaped?

471
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:18,030
No. I can't die here.

472
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:19,640
Oh Jang Mi is over there. Get her.

473
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:21,670
You're not going anywhere.
I won't let you hurt Jang Mi.

474
00:28:22,410 --> 00:28:23,540
That witch.

475
00:28:24,010 --> 00:28:25,380
I'm going to kill her.

476
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:29,410
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
